The paper deals with a secret sharing technique that has potential applications in secure and reliable storage of information on the Web and in sensor networks. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), Information Theory (cs.IT), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Computational Complexity (cs.CC), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). However, since the paper primarily focuses on a cryptographic technique, cs.CR is the most likely category, followed by cs.IT and cs.DS.
